      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Tag embedded subagent gap-fill rows as delivery mirrors",
        "body": "Fixes #87329\n\n## User-facing bug\nSubagent announce / embedded handoff gap-fill can append a user-visible assistant mirror using the child runtime provider and model metadata, such as `anthropic/claude-*`, instead of marking the row as an OpenClaw transcript-only delivery mirror. Replay filters only exclude `provider: \"openclaw\"` with `model: \"delivery-mirror\"` / `gateway-injected`, so a display-only mirror can later be replayed back into a provider turn. In conversations with provider-managed thinking/signature blocks, that stale mirror can surface as errors like \"thinking blocks cannot be modified.\"\n\n## Exact repro\nSource-level reproduction:\n\n1. Run `persistCliTurnTranscript` for an embedded assistant gap-fill with:\n   - `embeddedAssistantGapFill: true`\n   - `result.meta.agentMeta.provider: \"claude-cli\"` or another runtime provider\n   - visible final text in `result.meta.finalAssistantVisibleText`\n2. Before this fix, the appended transcript assistant row used `api: \"cli\"`, `provider: \"claude-cli\"`, and `model: \"opus\"`.\n3. That row is user-visible display state, not provider conversation state, so replay filters do not identify it as transcript-only.\n4. After this fix, the same gap-fill row is written as `api: \"openai-responses\"`, `provider: \"openclaw\"`, and `model: \"delivery-mirror\"`.\n\n## Fix summary\n- Changed embedded assistant gap-fill transcript persistence to write assistant mirrors as `openclaw/delivery-mirror`.\n- Kept normal CLI transcript persistence unchanged: non-gap-fill CLI replies still preserve real CLI provider/model metadata and usage.\n- Added regression coverage so the gap-fill path now asserts the transcript-only mirror metadata.\n\n## Targeted tests\n- Extended `src/agents/command/attempt-execution.cli.test.ts` to prove embedded gap-fill rows are tagged as `openclaw/delivery-mirror`.\n- Re-ran replay-history coverage to confirm `delivery-mirror` rows remain excluded from embedded provider replay.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Embedded subagent assistant gap-fill rows are now stored as OpenClaw delivery mirrors, so provider replay filters do not treat display-only text as provider conversation state.\n\nReal environment tested: Local OpenClaw checkout on branch `fix/subagent-announce-delivery-metadata`, commit `3ba0619f`, rebased onto `origin/main` at `be127318`.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n- `node node_modules/oxfmt/bin/oxfmt --write --threads=1 src/agents/command/attempt-execution.ts src/agents/command/attempt-execution.cli.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `CI=1 NODE_OPTIONS=--max-old-space-size=4096 OPENCLAW_VITEST_NO_OUTPUT_TIMEOUT_MS=120000 OPENCLAW_VITEST_NO_OUTPUT_HEARTBEAT_MS=10000 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs --run --maxWorkers 1 src/agents/command/attempt-execution.cli.test.ts`\n- `CI=1 NODE_OPTIONS=--max-old-space-size=4096 OPENCLAW_VITEST_NO_OUTPUT_TIMEOUT_MS=120000 OPENCLAW_VITEST_NO_OUTPUT_HEARTBEAT_MS=10000 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs --run --maxWorkers 1 src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/replay-history.test.ts src/agents/command/attempt-execution.cli.test.ts`\n- `codex review --base origin/main`\n\nEvidence after fix:\n- Command execution Vitest passed: `Test Files 2 passed (2)`, `Tests 62 passed (62)`.\n- Replay-history plus command execution Vitest passed: `Test Files 3 passed (3)`, `Tests 87 passed (87)`.\n- `git diff --check` passed.\n- `codex review --base origin/main` passed with no actionable regressions found.\n\nObserved result after fix: Embedded gap-fill transcript rows use `api: \"openai-responses\"`, `provider: \"openclaw\"`, and `model: \"delivery-mirror\"` while normal CLI transcript rows still preserve real provider/model metadata.\n\nWhat was not tested: `pnpm check:changed` did not reach changed-file checks because dependency installation hit npm registry DNS failures (`ENOTFOUND`) in the sandbox.\n\n## Not tested / known gaps\n- No live provider-managed thinking/signature conversation was replayed end to end; coverage is through transcript persistence and replay-history tests.\n\n## AI-assisted disclosure\nThis patch was prepared with AI assistance. I used local code inspection, targeted regression tests, and explicit command output to validate the behavior above.\n",
